  "messages": [
    {
      "id": "393011bdffc48a8ed9b9b9bb74909d34ed85d7f4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-06-14 15:24:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nPlease add a conf-sanity test case that verifies this is working correctly (ordering, etc).  I'm concerned that the ordering may be incorrect \"in the wild\" if interfaces were added to an OST after the initial config was written, though I'm not totally sure if this can happen or not.\n\nDid you consider having the MDT parse all of the interfaces in the config, and then configure all of the local ones, and assume any non-local interface is for failover?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "fc53be3649f67671195e6a6e30cc580902bad4d4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 101,
        "name": "Lai Siyao",
        "email": "lai.siyao@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "laisiyao"
      },
      "date": "2012-06-14 15:51:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: (1 inline comment)\n\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "3a3c6e748265f0a6a595d9b6fdbd1ae2aa23cc9d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 101,
        "name": "Lai Siyao",
        "email": "lai.siyao@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "laisiyao"
      },
      "date": "2012-06-15 03:45:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThere is already a test conf-sanity 21d for this, however our autotest system is not configured to a standalone mgs, so this test is always skipped. Chris need get involved to make it work.\n\nThe nids for OST is set at target mount time by checking all network interfaces, and then send to MGS to register target. So each time target is restarted, it will register with all current nids.\n\nThere is a command `lctl add_uuid ...`, but it's only for test, and in my understand this command can be run on client only.\n\nthe config MDT steals is OSC config to OST, so the nids are for OST, MDT can't know it by checking interfaces of its own.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
